    "client_msg_id": "3576F12D-39FC-4205-949D-64B7CD4B273F",
    "text": "There's some fantastic ideas at play here.\n\nThat idea of separate subnets for the true and false sides of the conditional node, which are allowed to produce differently typed outputs, is rather fun. I'm curious where else you're allowing subnets to be created.\n\nIf the live probe is based on selection, what happens when you select multiple things at once?\n\nAlso, I'm curious why the probe is a dedicated window, rather than every node showing live values all the time. Is it about visual noise / space? Or perf? Or some other tradeoff?",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1713759805.937119",
    "parent_user_id": "U03U0SCU5LH",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "SBjia",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "There's some fantastic ideas at play here.\n\nThat idea of separate subnets for the true and false sides of the conditional node, which are allowed to produce differently typed outputs, is rather fun. I'm curious where else you're allowing subnets to be created"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nIf the live probe is based on selection, what happens when you select multiple things at once?\n\nAlso, I'm curious why the probe is a dedicated window, rather than every node showing live values all the time. Is it about visual noise / space? Or perf? Or some other tradeoff?"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
