    "client_msg_id": "39268a28-7b07-4f67-b65f-4e97b02052c8",
    "text": "Yes, this is an interesting development. Its main weakness so far is the scarcity of nanopublications, which is caused by the need to create them manually, a rather unpleasant for humans. There is ongoing research on using LLMs to derive nanopublications from papers, but the obvious risk there is getting them wrong.\nI think the best future for nanopublications would be authors provide them along with papers. But I have no idea what would actually convince authors to do so.",
